messages.message: hello! I was working on this ticket (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/AUTO-119) and was wondering if anyone knew how to access the Accuracy Report page on the UI?

on mine, for some reason the BE `/bulk_status` endpoint keeps returning PENDING state and 0 for progress. The progress bar keeps hanging whenever i manually upload files as dataset, or when i run a test accuracy. Is there any prerequisite things I need such as permissions?
It might be an issue with your crafting sandbox. What's the sandbox name?
I see that your PID for `model-service` is high, which suggests it's repeatedly boot looping
Going into the logs, I see the AWS 401 permission issues, which I think is related to the crafting issues last week
I'm going to ssh into your box and see what's up
i see thanks for guiding me through this Paul! Ill take a look at the aws crafting issue threads

Now it looks like model-service is building now (https://instabase.sandboxes.site/logviewx/instabase/jadenlee/dev/daemon/model-service%40instabase). Once that's complete, you should be able to make a ground truth
